1
00:00:01,335 --> 00:00:02,753
[ CLICKING TONGUE ]

2
00:00:02,795 --> 00:00:05,923
PHLOX: I DIDN'T REALIZE
YOU SPOKE SLUG.

3
00:00:05,965 --> 00:00:08,634
I WISH I DID.

4
00:00:08,676 --> 00:00:10,218
SHE DOESN'T LOOK ANY BETTER,
DOES SHE?

5
00:00:10,260 --> 00:00:11,846
PHLOX: SHE?

6
00:00:11,887 --> 00:00:14,139
WE HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO DETERMINE ITS GENDER,

7
00:00:14,181 --> 00:00:16,016
IF IT HAS ONE.

8
00:00:16,057 --> 00:00:18,268
HOSHI: I SHOULD HAVE LEFT HER
WHERE I FOUND HER.

9
00:00:18,310 --> 00:00:21,146
PHLOX: NONSENSE. YOU'RE
ON A MISSION OF EXPLORATION.

10
00:00:21,188 --> 00:00:23,440
THERE'S SOMETHING TO BE LEARNED
FROM EVERY LIFE-FORM.

11
00:00:23,482 --> 00:00:25,651
SHE WASN'T MEANT TO BE
IN THIS ENVIRONMENT.

12
00:00:25,693 --> 00:00:29,822
PHLOX: I PROMISE TO DO MY BEST
TO KEEP IT ALIVE.

13
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:35,327
HE'S GONNA MAKE YOU ALL BETTER.

14
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:38,413
PHLOX: ACTUALLY, I WAS THINKING
MORE ABOUT MY PYRITHIAN BAT.

15
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:42,292
HE WON'T EAT ANYTHING
ONCE IT'S DEAD, HMM?

16
00:00:43,711 --> 00:00:46,129
TUCKER: WE'VE ROUTED SOME MORE
POWER TO SICK BAY.

17
00:00:46,171 --> 00:00:47,255
LET ME KNOW IF IT'S ENOUGH.

18
00:00:47,297 --> 00:00:49,341
PHLOX: THIS SHOULD DO FINE.

19
00:00:49,383 --> 00:00:51,259
TUCKER: HOW'S SLUGGO?

20
00:00:51,301 --> 00:00:55,138
HOSHI: DR. PHLOX THINKS
THIS ARGON LAMP SHOULD HELP.

21
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:58,266
SHE'S BARELY MOVED ALL DAY.

22
00:00:58,308 --> 00:01:00,561
TUCKER: WE'VE BEEN OUT HERE
FOR TWO WEEKS,

23
00:01:00,602 --> 00:01:03,104
AND THE ONLY FIRST CONTACT
WE'VE MADE

24
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:05,774
IS WITH A DYING WORM.

25
00:01:12,573 --> 00:01:17,202
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG ROAD ♪

26
00:01:17,244 --> 00:01:20,455
♪ GETTING FROM THERE TO HERE ♪

27
00:01:20,497 --> 00:01:24,251
♪ IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME ♪

28
00:01:24,292 --> 00:01:27,963
♪ BUT MY TIME IS FINALLY NEAR ♪

29
00:01:28,005 --> 00:01:32,342
♪ AND I WILL SEE MY DREAM
COME ALIVE AT LAST ♪

30
00:01:32,384 --> 00:01:36,055
♪ I WILL TOUCH THE SKY ♪

31
00:01:36,095 --> 00:01:40,017
♪ AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA
HOLD ME DOWN NO MORE ♪

32
00:01:40,059 --> 00:01:42,853
♪ NO, THEY'RE NOT GONNA
CHANGE MY MIND ♪

33
00:01:42,895 --> 00:01:46,147
♪ 'CAUSE I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

34
00:01:46,189 --> 00:01:47,816
♪ OF THE HEART ♪

35
00:01:47,858 --> 00:01:51,445
♪ I'M GOING WHERE MY HEART
WILL TAKE ME ♪

36
00:01:51,486 --> 00:01:56,241
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH TO BELIEVE ♪

37
00:01:56,283 --> 00:01:58,660
♪ I CAN DO ANYTHING ♪

38
00:01:58,702 --> 00:02:03,540
♪ I'VE GOT STRENGTH
OF THE SOUL ♪

39
00:02:03,582 --> 00:02:06,334
♪ AND NO ONE'S GONNA BEND
OR BREAK ME ♪

40
00:02:06,376 --> 00:02:12,132
♪ I CAN REACH ANY STAR ♪

41
00:02:12,173 --> 00:02:14,009
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

42
00:02:14,051 --> 00:02:16,344
♪ I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT, I'VE GOT ♪

43
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:19,723
♪ I'VE GOT FAITH ♪

44
00:02:19,765 --> 00:02:24,686
♪ FAITH OF THE HEART ♪

45
00:02:35,990 --> 00:02:37,532
[ SQUEAK ]

46
00:02:39,701 --> 00:02:41,202
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

47
00:02:41,244 --> 00:02:43,747
COME IN.

48
00:02:43,789 --> 00:02:45,874
T'POL: THE SCANS OF THE SECTORS
AHEAD--

49
00:02:45,916 --> 00:02:47,835
ARCHER: SHH!

50
00:02:47,876 --> 00:02:50,253
HEAR THAT?

51
00:02:50,295 --> 00:02:51,839
T'POL: HEAR WHAT?

52
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:55,050
ARCHER: A SQUEAK.
SOMETHING SQUEAKING.

53
00:02:55,092 --> 00:02:57,803
I THINK IT'S COMING
FROM UNDER THE DECK PLATING,

54
00:02:57,845 --> 00:03:00,889
BUT EVERY TIME I GET CLOSE
TO IT, IT STOPS.

55
00:03:00,931 --> 00:03:02,265
IF I CAN'T ISOLATE IT,

56
00:03:02,307 --> 00:03:04,685
I'M GONNA HAVE TO TEAR
THE WHOLE FLOORING UP.

57
00:03:04,726 --> 00:03:08,229
THAT WOULD BE UNFORTUNATE.

58
00:03:08,271 --> 00:03:10,732
THE SCANS OF THE SECTORS AHEAD
INDICATE LITTLE CHANCE

59
00:03:10,774 --> 00:03:12,026
OF FINDING INHABITED PLANETS.

60
00:03:12,067 --> 00:03:15,529
ARCHER: WELL, HOW ABOUT
THE VULCAN STARCHARTS?

61
00:03:15,570 --> 00:03:16,864
T'POL: WE HAVE LIMITED DATA

62
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:18,782
ON THE COURSE THAT STARFLEET
ASSIGNED YOU.

63
00:03:18,824 --> 00:03:21,785
THERE ARE THOUSANDS
OF STAR SYSTEMS ALONG THIS PATH.

64
00:03:21,827 --> 00:03:23,620
THERE MUST HAVE BEEN SOMETHING

65
00:03:23,662 --> 00:03:25,497
THAT PIQUED
YOUR PEOPLE'S INTEREST--

66
00:03:25,539 --> 00:03:29,292
A SENTIENT SPECIES,
A TRINARY STAR CLUSTER.

67
00:03:29,334 --> 00:03:30,544
T'POL: WE DON'T SELECT
OUR DESTINATIONS

68
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:33,047
BY WHAT PIQUES OUR INTEREST.

69
00:03:33,088 --> 00:03:37,676
VULCANS ALWAYS NEED
A LOGICAL AND PRAGMATIC REASON.

70
00:03:37,718 --> 00:03:40,971
T'POL: MY PEOPLE DON'T SHARE
YOUR ENTHUSIASM FOR EXPLORATION.

71
00:03:41,013 --> 00:03:43,765
[ SQUEAKING ]

72
00:03:46,518 --> 00:03:49,146
T'POL: SPACE IS VAST, CAPTAIN.

73
00:03:49,188 --> 00:03:50,438
I'M SURE YOU'RE AWARE

74
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:53,358
THAT ONLY ONE OUT OF
EVERY 43,000 PLANETS

75
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:54,693
SUPPORTS INTELLIGENT LIFE.

76
00:03:54,735 --> 00:03:59,990
ARCHER: I TOOK EXOBIOLOGY.
I KNOW THE STATISTICS.

77
00:04:00,032 --> 00:04:01,575
BUT WE'RE TRAVELING AT WARP 5.

78
00:04:01,616 --> 00:04:03,368
THERE'S GOT TO BE
SOMEONE OUT HERE.

79
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:04,369
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

80
00:04:04,411 --> 00:04:08,331
COME IN.

81
00:04:08,373 --> 00:04:10,417
HOSHI: I'M SORRY.

82
00:04:11,793 --> 00:04:14,796
T'POL: I'LL LEAVE YOU
TO YOUR EXPLORING.

83
00:04:17,674 --> 00:04:18,967
ARCHER: TRIP TELLS ME

84
00:04:19,009 --> 00:04:20,844
THAT SLUGGO'S NOT
FARING TOO WELL.

85
00:04:20,886 --> 00:04:23,889
HOSHI: NO, SIR, BUT THE DOCTOR'S
DOING THE BEST HE CAN.

86
00:04:23,931 --> 00:04:27,142
SIR, MY QUARTERS
ARE ON "E" DECK,

87
00:04:27,184 --> 00:04:29,061
STARBOARD SECTION 5.

88
00:04:29,103 --> 00:04:30,229
YES.

89
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,981
THE STARS ARE GOING
THE WRONG WAY, SIR.

90
00:04:33,982 --> 00:04:35,400
WRONG WAY?

91
00:04:35,442 --> 00:04:39,988
ON BOTH MY TRAINING TOURS,
I HAD PORT-SIDE QUARTERS.

92
00:04:40,030 --> 00:04:42,407
I'M HAVING TROUBLE SLEEPING.

93
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:44,201
BECAUSE YOU'RE ON
THE WRONG SIDE--

94
00:04:44,243 --> 00:04:46,578
THE WRONG SIDE OF THE SHIP,
YES, SIR.

95
00:04:46,620 --> 00:04:48,122
I SPOKE WITH ENSIGN PORTER.

96
00:04:48,163 --> 00:04:50,624
HE SAID HE'D BE WILLING
TO SWITCH WITH YOUR PERMISSION.

97
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:52,167
YOU GOT IT.

98
00:04:52,209 --> 00:04:57,505
CAN'T HAVE MY COM OFFICER
FALLING ASLEEP ON THE BRIDGE.

99
00:04:57,547 --> 00:04:59,925
APPRECIATE IT, CAPTAIN.

100
00:05:01,551 --> 00:05:04,304
IS THERE SOMETHING ELSE, HOSHI?

101
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:07,099
NO, SIR. THANK YOU.

102
00:05:11,478 --> 00:05:12,813
[ SQUEAK ]

103
00:05:15,523 --> 00:05:16,817
READY?

104
00:05:16,858 --> 00:05:20,445
TRAVIS: FORE AND AFT
TARGET SCANNERS ARE ALIGNED.

105
00:05:20,487 --> 00:05:24,658
REED: ACTIVATING SIMULATION J-6.

106
00:05:30,289 --> 00:05:31,456
REED: TARGET ACQUIRED.

107
00:05:31,498 --> 00:05:32,791
TRAVIS: SIMULATED LAUNCH.

108
00:05:35,794 --> 00:05:37,754
FIVE SECONDS TO IMPACT.

109
00:05:37,796 --> 00:05:43,051
THREE, TWO, ONE.

110
00:05:45,512 --> 00:05:47,097
REED: WONDERFUL.

111
00:05:47,139 --> 00:05:49,432
TRAVIS: WE'RE ONLY OFF
BY THREE METERS.

112
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:51,018
REED: ONLY THREE METERS?

113
00:05:51,059 --> 00:05:52,644
THREE METERS COULD MEAN
THE DIFFERENCE

114
00:05:52,686 --> 00:05:55,105
BETWEEN HITTING A WEAPONS PORT
AND A WARP CORE.

115
00:05:55,147 --> 00:05:57,858
INSTEAD OF DISABLING A VESSEL,
WE'D END UP DESTROYING IT,

116
00:05:57,899 --> 00:06:00,027
AND PROBABLY OURSELVES
IN THE PROCESS.

117
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:02,237
TRAVIS: WE'LL GET IT RIGHT.

118
00:06:02,279 --> 00:06:04,948
REED: ALL THIS SHOULD HAVE BEEN
DEALT WITH BEFORE WE LEFT EARTH.

119
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:08,035
HAVE THEY DETECTED ANY INHABITED
PLANETS OR VESSELS?

120
00:06:08,076 --> 00:06:08,994
TRAVIS: NOT YET.

121
00:06:09,036 --> 00:06:10,287
REED: GOOD.

122
00:06:10,329 --> 00:06:12,206
TRAVIS: I HOPE YOU DON'T
EXPECT EVERYONE

123
00:06:12,247 --> 00:06:15,292
WE RUN INTO OUT HERE
TO BE HOSTILE.

124
00:06:15,334 --> 00:06:17,711
IN 23 YEARS, I DON'T THINK
MY FOLKS RAN INTO PROBLEMS

125
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:20,214
MORE THAN A HALF-DOZEN TIMES.

126
00:06:20,255 --> 00:06:22,507
REED: I DON'T BELIEVE YOU WERE
EVER OUT QUITE THIS FAR.

127
00:06:22,549 --> 00:06:25,093
TRAVIS: DO YOU THINK
THAT MAKES A DIFFERENCE?

128
00:06:25,135 --> 00:06:27,470
REED: ALL I DO KNOW
IS THAT UNTIL WE GET

129
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:29,388
THESE TARGETING SCANNERS
WORKING PROPERLY,

130
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:32,142
THE FARTHER WE ARE
FROM EVERYONE ELSE, THE BETTER.

131
00:06:32,184 --> 00:06:33,227
[ TRAVIS CHUCKLES ]

132
00:06:33,268 --> 00:06:34,728
SEEMS LIKE EVERYBODY ELSE
ONBOARD

133
00:06:34,769 --> 00:06:36,479
IS ITCHING FOR A FIRST CONTACT.

134
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:39,858
ARCHER: HOW'S IT GOING?

135
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,526
REED: NOT WELL, SIR.

136
00:06:41,568 --> 00:06:46,365
WE'VE CORRECTED THE PROBLEM,
BUT WE'RE STILL OFF BY .02%.

137
00:06:46,405 --> 00:06:48,033
IT'S UNACCEPTABLE.

138
00:06:48,075 --> 00:06:50,618
ARCHER: ARE YOU SURE IT'S NOT
THE SIMULATIONS THAT ARE OFF?

139
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:53,830
REED: THERE'S ONLY
ONE WAY TO FIND OUT.

140
00:06:53,872 --> 00:06:57,584
ARCHER: HOW LONG WOULD IT TAKE
TO ARM A FEW TORPEDOES?

141
00:06:57,625 --> 00:06:59,586
REED: MOMENTS, SIR.

142
00:07:04,049 --> 00:07:06,425
ARCHER: ARCHER TO T'POL.
T'POL: YES, SIR.

143
00:07:06,467 --> 00:07:08,178
ARCHER: PREPARE TO
DROP OUT OF WARP.

144
00:07:08,220 --> 00:07:10,889
IT'S TIME FOR A LITTLE
TARGET PRACTICE.

145
00:07:10,931 --> 00:07:12,307
T'POL: ACKNOWLEDGED.

146
00:07:12,349 --> 00:07:13,767
REED: THANK YOU, CAPTAIN.

147
00:07:13,808 --> 00:07:15,352
COME ON, TRAVIS.

148
00:07:15,394 --> 00:07:18,813
WE'VE GOT TO FIND MR. REED
SOMETHING TO BLOW UP.

149
00:07:28,198 --> 00:07:31,451
[ BEEPING ]

150
00:07:31,492 --> 00:07:34,662
ARCHER: LOAD ANOTHER ONE.
LET'S TRY AGAIN.

151
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:39,251
REED: ROTATE THE TARGETING AXIS
BY .5 MICRONS.

152
00:07:39,293 --> 00:07:40,627
TRAVIS: .5 MICRONS.

153
00:08:03,650 --> 00:08:05,360
MR. REED.

154
00:08:08,447 --> 00:08:11,616
REED: IF I REFOCUS
THE INFRARED SCANNER,

155
00:08:11,658 --> 00:08:12,784
I MIGHT BE ABLE TO COMPENSATE.

156
00:08:12,826 --> 00:08:15,120
HOW LONG WILL THAT TAKE?

157
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:17,414
THE BETTER PART OF A DAY.

158
00:08:17,456 --> 00:08:21,042
ARCHER: RESUME COURSE, ENSIGN.

159
00:08:21,084 --> 00:08:22,585
REED: SIR.

160
00:08:22,627 --> 00:08:25,630
ARCHER: WE'RE NOT GONNA SIT
ON OUR BUTT FOR 24 HOURS.

161
00:08:25,672 --> 00:08:27,048
MAKE YOUR MODIFICATIONS.

162
00:08:27,090 --> 00:08:29,676
WE'LL RUN ANOTHER TEST
FIRST CHANCE WE GET.

163
00:08:32,471 --> 00:08:34,597
TUCKER: ANYONE SITTING HERE?

164
00:08:34,639 --> 00:08:37,809
PHLOX: NO. PLEASE SIT DOWN.
SIT DOWN.

165
00:08:37,851 --> 00:08:39,686
TUCKER: SLUGGO ANY BETTER?

166
00:08:39,727 --> 00:08:41,271
PHLOX: I'M AFRAID NOT.

167
00:08:41,313 --> 00:08:43,940
TRY THE POTATOES.
THEY'RE DELICIOUS.

168
00:08:49,029 --> 00:08:50,655
RESEQUENCED PROTEIN.

169
00:08:50,697 --> 00:08:53,700
YES.
THE FLAVOR'S REMARKABLE.

170
00:08:53,741 --> 00:08:55,369
ON MY HOMEWORLD,

171
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:57,912
PEOPLE WOULD NEVER THINK
OF SPEAKING DURING A MEAL.

172
00:08:57,954 --> 00:09:00,374
CONSIDER IT A WASTE OF TIME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

173
00:09:00,415 --> 00:09:01,541
IT'S TAKEN ME A WHILE,

174
00:09:01,582 --> 00:09:03,126
BUT I'VE GROWN
QUITE ATTACHED TO IT.

175
00:09:03,168 --> 00:09:05,670
TUCKER: WASTING TIME SEEMS
TO BE ALL WE'VE BEEN DOING.

176
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:07,506
STARTING TO GET A LITTLE ANTSY.

177
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:09,883
PHLOX: ANTSY?

178
00:09:09,924 --> 00:09:11,551
TUCKER: RESTLESS.
PHLOX: MM.

179
00:09:11,592 --> 00:09:12,927
TUCKER: WE'VE BEEN ON THE MOVE
FOR TWO WEEKS

180
00:09:12,969 --> 00:09:14,595
AND HAVEN'T SEEN A DAMN THING.

181
00:09:14,637 --> 00:09:18,683
[ PHLOX CHUCKLES ]
EVERY MOMENT'S BEEN
AN ADVENTURE FOR ME.

182
00:09:18,725 --> 00:09:21,728
HUMANS ARE SO UNPREDICTABLE.

183
00:09:21,769 --> 00:09:24,731
HAVE YOU SEEN THE QUANTITIES
OF FOOD CREWMAN NAMOD CONSUMES?

184
00:09:24,772 --> 00:09:27,567
NOT REALLY.

185
00:09:27,608 --> 00:09:30,529
HAVE YOU SMELLED ENSIGN SOCORRO
AFTER SHE EXERCISES?

186
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,155
UH...

187
00:09:32,197 --> 00:09:33,407
PHLOX: SHE GIVES OFF A FRAGRANCE

188
00:09:33,448 --> 00:09:35,783
NOT UNLIKE THE ADRENAL GLAND
OF A NAUSICAAN.

189
00:09:35,825 --> 00:09:38,745
AND CREWMEN BENNETT
AND HAYDEN OVER THERE--

190
00:09:38,786 --> 00:09:40,121
DO YOU SEE THEM?

191
00:09:40,163 --> 00:09:44,543
IF I'M NOT MISTAKEN, THEY ARE
PREPARING TO MATE.

192
00:09:46,545 --> 00:09:48,671
DO YOU THINK THEY MIGHT
LET ME WATCH?

193
00:09:50,340 --> 00:09:52,717
IT'S GOOD TO SEE
YOU'RE ENJOYING YOURSELF.

194
00:09:52,759 --> 00:09:55,178
MMM. MMM!

195
00:10:00,767 --> 00:10:03,228
[ BEEPING ]

196
00:10:03,270 --> 00:10:04,854
BRIDGE TO CAPTAIN ARCHER.

197
00:10:04,896 --> 00:10:06,647
ARCHER: HOW BIG IS IT?

198
00:10:06,689 --> 00:10:08,733
T'POL: APPROXIMATELY 92 METERS
IN LENGTH.

199
00:10:08,775 --> 00:10:10,693
ARCHER: DOESN'T SEEM
TO BE MOVING VERY FAST.

200
00:10:10,735 --> 00:10:12,487
T'POL: IT'S NOT MOVING AT ALL.

201
00:10:12,529 --> 00:10:14,822
ARCHER: THAT'S ODD.

202
00:10:14,864 --> 00:10:16,491
WHERE'S THE NEAREST STAR SYSTEM?

203
00:10:16,533 --> 00:10:18,577
T'POL: ALMOST THREE
LIGHT-YEARS AWAY.

204
00:10:18,618 --> 00:10:21,413
THEY COULD BE RUNNING SOME KIND
OF A DEEP-SPACE EXPERIMENT.

205
00:10:21,455 --> 00:10:23,248
MAYBE WE SHOULD GO HAVE A LOOK.

206
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:25,750
T'POL: IF YOU INSIST ON
ALLOWING YOUR CURIOSITY

207
00:10:25,792 --> 00:10:27,794
TO DICTATE YOUR ACTIONS.

208
00:10:27,835 --> 00:10:29,588
WE INSIST.

209
00:10:35,218 --> 00:10:37,345
TRAVIS: RANGE--5,000 KILOMETERS.

210
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:40,890
T'POL: THE VESSEL'S HULL
IS COMPRISED

211
00:10:40,932 --> 00:10:43,768
OF TRITANIUM
AND DISILICON POLYMERS.

212
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:47,188
TUCKER: I'M NOT GETTING ANYTHING
ON THEIR PROPULSION SYSTEM.

213
00:10:47,230 --> 00:10:49,232
BUT IT MAY BE OFFLINE.

214
00:10:49,274 --> 00:10:50,733
IT'S SOMETHING, ISN'T IT?

215
00:10:50,775 --> 00:10:53,820
REED: IF THEY HAVE WEAPONS,
THEY'RE NOT CHARGED.

216
00:10:53,861 --> 00:10:55,780
ARCHER: ANY COM ACTIVITY?

217
00:10:55,822 --> 00:10:57,616
[ BEEPING ]

218
00:10:57,657 --> 00:10:58,825
HOSHI: NO, SIR.

219
00:11:01,202 --> 00:11:05,873
ARCHER: RUN THIS THROUGH
THE TRANSLATION MATRIX.

220
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:08,376
MY NAME IS JONATHAN ARCHER.

221
00:11:08,418 --> 00:11:12,297
I'M CAPTAIN
OF THE STARSHIP<i> ENTERPRISE.</i>

222
00:11:12,339 --> 00:11:15,800
WE'RE ON A MISSION
OF PEACEFUL EXPLORATION.

223
00:11:15,842 --> 00:11:17,427
MAN: EARTH.

224
00:11:17,469 --> 00:11:18,803
ARCHER: OH.

225
00:11:18,845 --> 00:11:23,308
WE COME FROM THE PLANET EARTH.

226
00:11:23,350 --> 00:11:25,226
WE ARE SENDING YOU A PULSAR GRID

227
00:11:25,268 --> 00:11:28,313
THAT SHOULD HELP YOU
LOCATE OUR STAR SYSTEM.

228
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:35,570
DID YOU ROTATE THE FREQUENCIES?

229
00:11:35,612 --> 00:11:39,240
I'LL TRY IT AGAIN.

230
00:11:39,282 --> 00:11:42,369
NO RESPONSE, SIR.

231
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:45,205
TUCKER: CAPTAIN,
MIND IF I PUSH IN

232
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:46,873
ON THE VENTING PORTS
AROUND THAT HATCH?

233
00:11:46,914 --> 00:11:48,749
ARCHER: GO AHEAD.

234
00:11:52,795 --> 00:11:56,132
TRAVIS: ARE THOSE VENTING PORTS
OR HULL BREACHES?

235
00:11:56,174 --> 00:11:57,342
ARCHER: BRING US IN
A LITTLE CLOSER, TRAVIS.

236
00:11:57,384 --> 00:12:00,011
LET'S GET A LOOK
AT THE OTHER SIDE.

237
00:12:08,769 --> 00:12:10,605
ARCHER: THOSE LOOK
LIKE SCORCH MARKS.

238
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:13,858
THE RESIDUE INDICATES OXIDATION
AND THERMAL SHOCK EFFECTS.

239
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:17,820
IT COULD BE THE RESULT
OF A HIGH-YIELD PARTICLE IMPACT.

240
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:19,447
YOU MEAN WEAPONS.

241
00:12:19,489 --> 00:12:20,699
POSSIBLY.

242
00:12:20,739 --> 00:12:24,202
ARE WE CLOSE ENOUGH
TO SCAN FOR BIO-SIGNS?

243
00:12:24,244 --> 00:12:26,538
T'POL: YES, BUT SCANNING
THEIR SHIP'S INTERIOR

244
00:12:26,580 --> 00:12:29,374
MIGHT BE SEEN
AS A VIOLATION OF PRIVACY.

245
00:12:31,834 --> 00:12:32,835
ANYTHING?

246
00:12:33,836 --> 00:12:35,171
TUCKER: IF THERE<i> IS</i> ANYONE HOME,

247
00:12:35,213 --> 00:12:38,258
YOU CAN BET THEY KNOW
WE'RE OUT HERE.

248
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:40,635
REED: THEN WHY HAVEN'T
THEY RESPONDED?

249
00:12:40,677 --> 00:12:44,222
T'POL: NOT EVERYONE
CHOOSES TO ANSWER THE DOOR
WHEN THEY HEAR A KNOCK.

250
00:12:44,264 --> 00:12:47,100
IT WOULD BE BEST TO RESUME
OUR PREVIOUS COURSE.

251
00:12:47,141 --> 00:12:49,852
[ ARCHER SIGHS ]

252
00:12:49,894 --> 00:12:52,355
SEE IF YOU CAN FIND
ANOTHER HATCH.

253
00:12:58,236 --> 00:12:59,446
ARCHER: DIAMETER?

254
00:12:59,487 --> 00:13:02,907
TUCKER: .9 METERS.

255
00:13:02,949 --> 00:13:05,159
ARCHER: SCAN FOR BIO-SIGNS.

256
00:13:10,624 --> 00:13:13,418
THERE ARE A NUMBER
OF LIFE-FORMS ABOARD.

257
00:13:13,460 --> 00:13:15,044
ARCHER: HUMANOID?

258
00:13:15,086 --> 00:13:16,129
THEIR CELLULAR ACTIVITY
IS BELOW

259
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:17,964
THE THRESHOLD OF YOUR SENSORS.

260
00:13:18,005 --> 00:13:21,008
TRAVIS: MAYBE THEY'RE
IN TROUBLE--SICK OR SOMETHING.

261
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:23,762
MAYBE THEY'RE NOT INTERESTED
IN VISITORS.

262
00:13:26,765 --> 00:13:29,058
ARCHER: MR. REED, HOW LONG
TO PREP A SHUTTLE?

263
00:13:29,100 --> 00:13:30,644
REED: HALF AN HOUR.

264
00:13:30,685 --> 00:13:33,938
T'POL: THERE ARE A NUMBER OF
PROTOCOLS WE HAVEN'T TRIED.

265
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:35,148
ARCHER: GET STARTED.

266
00:13:35,189 --> 00:13:36,608
HOSHI: SHE MAY HAVE
A POINT, CAPTAIN.

267
00:13:36,650 --> 00:13:39,944
I COULD TRY HAILING THEM
ON THE THETA-BAND FREQUENCIES.

268
00:13:39,986 --> 00:13:41,070
ARCHER: SUIT UP, ENSIGN.

269
00:13:41,112 --> 00:13:43,657
ME, SIR?

270
00:13:43,698 --> 00:13:45,325
ARCHER: SHIP IS YOURS.

271
00:13:54,959 --> 00:13:56,919
ARCHER: IS THERE
A PROBLEM, COMMANDER?

272
00:13:56,961 --> 00:13:58,505
TUCKER: I WANT TO GO WITH YOU.

273
00:13:58,546 --> 00:14:00,923
ARCHER: I'M BRINGING
A TRANSLATOR
AND A SECURITY OFFICER.

274
00:14:00,965 --> 00:14:02,342
WHY WOULD I NEED
AN ENGINEER?

275
00:14:02,383 --> 00:14:04,302
TUCKER: WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
YOU CAN OPEN THE HATCH

276
00:14:04,344 --> 00:14:06,387
OR TURN THE LIGHTS ON,
FOR THAT MATTER?

277
00:14:06,429 --> 00:14:07,806
ARCHER: WE'VE GOT BEACONS, TRIP.

278
00:14:07,846 --> 00:14:09,432
TUCKER: WELL, THAT SHIP COULD
HAVE A LOT OF DECKS.

279
00:14:09,474 --> 00:14:12,935
YOU MIGHT NEED SOMEBODY TO HELP
YOU FIGURE OUT THE TURBOLIFTS.

280
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:16,105
OKAY, I'VE GOT A BETTER REASON
WHY YOU NEED AN ENGINEER.

281
00:14:16,147 --> 00:14:17,691
'CAUSE YOUR ENGINEER

282
00:14:17,732 --> 00:14:19,275
SIGNED ONTO THIS
MISSION OF EXPLORATION

283
00:14:19,317 --> 00:14:20,943
SO HE COULD DO
A LITTLE EXPLORING.

284
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:23,279
HE DIDN'T SIGN ON
SO HE COULD SIT IN ENGINEERING

285
00:14:23,321 --> 00:14:24,864
WHILE YOU THREE GET
TO BREAK INTO THAT SHIP.

286
00:14:24,905 --> 00:14:26,282
ARCHER: WE'RE NOT BREAKING IN.

287
00:14:26,324 --> 00:14:28,159
WE'RE JUST GOING TO SEE
IF EVERYTHING'S OKAY.

288
00:14:28,201 --> 00:14:30,537
TUCKER: YOU'RE CHOMPING AT THE
BIT TO FIND OUT WHAT'S IN THERE.

289
00:14:30,578 --> 00:14:31,746
WHY SHOULD I BE ANY DIFFERENT?

290
00:14:31,788 --> 00:14:33,164
ARCHER: WE JUST
GOT OUT HERE, TRIP.

291
00:14:34,999 --> 00:14:37,251
THERE'S GONNA BE PLENTY OF TIME
TO GO EXPLORING.

292
00:14:37,293 --> 00:14:39,170
RIGHT NOW,
I NEED YOU ON<i> ENTERPRISE</i>

293
00:14:39,212 --> 00:14:41,464
DOWN WITH YOUR ENGINE.

294
00:14:41,506 --> 00:14:44,258
THE SHIP'S A LITTLE YOUNG TO BE
WITHOUT HER CHIEF ENGINEER.

295
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:53,059
WHEN I USED TO DREAM
ABOUT THIS MISSION,

296
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:56,229
THE LAST THING I ENVISIONED
WAS HAVING A VULCAN ONBOARD

297
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:58,857
WHO CONTINUOUSLY SUCKED
THE AIR OUT OF THE ROOM.

298
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:04,529
WELL...SHE'S RIGHT.

299
00:15:04,571 --> 00:15:08,783
WHOEVER'S ON THAT SHIP
MIGHT NOT WANT US NOSING AROUND.

300
00:15:08,825 --> 00:15:12,620
BUT I CAN'T ASSUME
THAT'S THE CASE, CAN I?

301
00:15:12,662 --> 00:15:14,414
MAYBE THEY COULD USE OUR HELP.

302
00:15:14,455 --> 00:15:15,874
COMPUTER, PAUSE.

303
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:17,208
YOU KNOW. HEY.

304
00:15:17,250 --> 00:15:20,086
YOU KNOW THAT YOU AND CHEDDAR
DON'T GET ALONG.

305
00:15:20,127 --> 00:15:24,006
AH.

306
00:15:24,048 --> 00:15:27,051
RESUME PERSONAL LOG.

307
00:15:27,093 --> 00:15:29,011
BEFORE WE LEFT,
ADMIRAL FORREST SAID

308
00:15:29,053 --> 00:15:32,390
WE'D BE MAKING HISTORY
WITH EVERY LIGHT-YEAR,

309
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:35,226
BUT WE'RE NOT GONNA DO THAT
SITTING ON OUR HANDS.

310
00:15:35,268 --> 00:15:37,437
[ DOOR CHIMES ]

311
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:38,938
COMPUTER, PAUSE.

312
00:15:38,979 --> 00:15:42,609
COME IN.

313
00:15:42,650 --> 00:15:44,444
ARCHER: ENSIGN.
HOSHI: SORRY TO BOTHER YOU, SIR.

314
00:15:44,485 --> 00:15:46,070
ARCHER: IT'S NOT A PROBLEM.

315
00:15:46,112 --> 00:15:47,321
CHEESE?

316
00:15:47,363 --> 00:15:49,031
NO, THANK YOU.

317
00:15:49,073 --> 00:15:51,910
EVERYTHING WORK OUT
ALL RIGHT?

318
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:52,993
SIR?

319
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:54,995
WITH THE SWAPPING QUARTERS?

320
00:15:55,037 --> 00:15:59,166
HOSHI: YES, IT'S FINE.
THANK YOU.

321
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:00,460
I WAS THINKING, CAPTAIN,

322
00:16:00,501 --> 00:16:02,086
I MIGHT BE
A LOT MORE HELPFUL TO YOU

323
00:16:02,128 --> 00:16:04,130
IF I STAY HERE
AND KEEP AN OPEN COM LINK.

324
00:16:04,171 --> 00:16:05,506
THAT WAY, I'LL HAVE

325
00:16:05,548 --> 00:16:07,550
IMMEDIATE ACCESS
TO THE LINGUISTIC DATABASE.

326
00:16:07,592 --> 00:16:10,094
CAN'T YOU TIE
YOUR UNIVERSAL TRANSLATOR

327
00:16:10,136 --> 00:16:12,346
INTO THE DATABASE
THROUGH THE COM?

328
00:16:12,388 --> 00:16:13,932
IT'S NOT THE SAME.

329
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:16,517
THE LAG TIME IS TRIPLED.

330
00:16:16,559 --> 00:16:18,853
WELL, I'D RATHER
WAIT A FEW SECONDS

331
00:16:18,895 --> 00:16:21,606
IF IT MEANS HAVING YOU ON SITE.

332
00:16:21,648 --> 00:16:25,067
FOR ALL WE KNOW,
THE U.T. WON'T WORK.

333
00:16:25,109 --> 00:16:27,987
YOU'LL BE OUR ONLY BACKUP.
ANYWAY, IT SHOULD BE EXCITING.

334
00:16:28,028 --> 00:16:30,907
HALF THE CREW WOULD GIVE THEIR
EYETEETH TO BE GOING OVER THERE.

335
00:16:32,492 --> 00:16:34,368
WHAT'S WRONG?

336
00:16:36,579 --> 00:16:37,789
THE ENVIRONMENTAL SUITS.

337
00:16:37,831 --> 00:16:42,126
THEY MAKE ME
A LITTLE...CLAUSTROPHOBIC.

338
00:16:42,168 --> 00:16:45,755
CLAUSTROPHOBIC?

339
00:16:45,797 --> 00:16:48,758
AND YOU TOOK A JOB
ON A SPACESHIP?

340
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:50,510
HOSHI: YOU TALKED ME
INTO IT, REMEMBER?

341
00:16:50,551 --> 00:16:53,137
ARCHER: I DON'T RECALL READING
ABOUT ANY PROBLEMS

342
00:16:53,179 --> 00:16:55,014
DURING YOUR ZERO-G TRAINING.

343
00:16:55,055 --> 00:16:58,100
HOSHI: OH, I JUST--I-I BIT
MY LIP AND GOT THROUGH IT.

344
00:16:58,142 --> 00:17:01,521
WELL, YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO BITE YOUR LIP AGAIN.

345
00:17:01,562 --> 00:17:04,774
I NEED YOU OVER THERE.

346
00:17:04,816 --> 00:17:06,025
YES, SIR.

347
00:17:10,530 --> 00:17:14,241
WHAT IS IT, HOSHI?

348
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:17,537
IS SOMETHING ELSE WRONG?

349
00:17:17,578 --> 00:17:20,080
NO. I'D BETTER GET BACK
TO THE LAUNCH BAY.

350
00:17:20,122 --> 00:17:21,875
ARCHER: HANG ON,
I'LL COME WITH YOU.

351
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:23,417
[ PORTHOS BARKS ]

352
00:17:23,459 --> 00:17:25,628
[ WHIMPERING ]

353
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:30,424
ARCHER: THAT'S
THE LAST TIME, PORTHOS.

354
00:17:35,722 --> 00:17:38,140
ARCHER: GOING TO WAR,
LIEUTENANT?

355
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:40,142
REED: CAN'T BE TOO CAREFUL, SIR.

356
00:17:40,184 --> 00:17:42,144
ARCHER: YOU'VE SEEN TOO MANY
SCIENCE-FICTION MOVIES.

357
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:44,146
WE JUST NEED
THE THREE PHASE PISTOLS.

358
00:17:44,188 --> 00:17:45,231
PUT THE RIFLES BACK.

359
00:17:45,272 --> 00:17:46,941
WHAT ARE YOU RATED FOR?

360
00:17:46,983 --> 00:17:49,777
HOSHI: I'VE BEEN CLEARED
ON EM SIDEARMS

361
00:17:49,819 --> 00:17:51,320
AND CLASS-3 PULSE RIFLES.

362
00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:55,115
I'VE NEVER SEEN ONE OF THOSE.

363
00:17:55,157 --> 00:17:57,535
ARCHER: MALCOLM WILL CHECK YOU
OUT ON IT FIRST CHANCE HE GETS.

364
00:17:59,704 --> 00:18:02,623
DON'T WORRY. IT HANDLES
PRETTY MUCH LIKE AN EM-33.

365
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:10,423
HOSHI: IS THIS NECESSARY?

366
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:12,967
ARCHER: JUST A PRECAUTION.

367
00:18:34,530 --> 00:18:36,115
JUST OUR LUCK.

368
00:18:36,156 --> 00:18:39,493
NO RELEASE.
SHOULDN'T BE A PROBLEM, THOUGH.

369
00:18:39,535 --> 00:18:43,289
I CAN PLACE MICROCHARGES
HERE AND HERE.

370
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:45,249
HOLD ON A SECOND, MALCOLM.

371
00:19:00,222 --> 00:19:01,432
SORRY.

372
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:02,934
HOSHI:<i> ENTERPRISE,</i> 
WE'VE GOT ACCESS.

373
00:19:02,976 --> 00:19:05,227
WE'RE BOARDING THE VESSEL.

374
00:19:21,327 --> 00:19:23,329
[ BEEPING ]

375
00:19:26,373 --> 00:19:28,626
HOSHI: WELL, AT LEAST WE KNOW
THEY'RE BIPEDS.

376
00:19:28,668 --> 00:19:30,419
REED: WHAT GIVES YOU THAT IDEA?

377
00:19:30,461 --> 00:19:33,172
HOSHI: THE LADDER.

378
00:19:33,213 --> 00:19:34,298
ARCHER: COME ON.

379
00:19:34,340 --> 00:19:38,552
NITROGEN-METHANE ATMOSPHERE...

380
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:43,141
AND IT'S COLD--
MINUS-20 DEGREES.

381
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:46,310
HOSHI: THERE'S POWER
GOING THROUGH HERE,

382
00:19:46,352 --> 00:19:48,896
BUT NOT MUCH OF IT.

383
00:19:48,938 --> 00:19:50,148
REED: CAPTAIN.

384
00:19:57,613 --> 00:20:00,449
ARCHER: MOLECULES LOOK
LIKE AMINO ACIDS.

385
00:20:00,491 --> 00:20:02,118
HOSHI: BLOOD?

386
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:12,086
[ WHIRRING ]

387
00:20:48,288 --> 00:20:50,958
REED: SOME SORT OF HYDRAULICS.

388
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,586
ARCHER: WHATEVER IT IS,
IT HASN'T BEEN HERE VERY LONG.

389
00:20:55,421 --> 00:20:57,381
AAH!

390
00:20:57,423 --> 00:20:59,383
AAH!

391
00:21:00,551 --> 00:21:02,261
[ HOSHI PANTING ]

392
00:21:08,601 --> 00:21:10,686
ARCHER: HOSHI, WHERE YOU GOING?

393
00:21:10,728 --> 00:21:13,147
HOSHI: I DON'T THINK
YOU NEED A TRANSLATOR!

394
00:21:13,189 --> 00:21:15,399
ARCHER: STAY HERE.

395
00:21:15,441 --> 00:21:20,029
REED: THEIR BODIES
ARE BEING FLUSHED OUT
WITH SOME KIND OF FLUID.

396
00:21:20,071 --> 00:21:23,365
ARCHER: ARE THEY ALL--
REED: ALL DEAD, SIR.

397
00:21:23,407 --> 00:21:25,701
I'M AFRAID SO.

398
00:21:26,786 --> 00:21:28,204
PHLOX: THEY'RE CLEAN.

399
00:21:31,331 --> 00:21:32,458
T'POL: HOW MANY?

400
00:21:32,499 --> 00:21:34,293
ARCHER: I DON'T KNOW.
ABOUT A DOZEN.

401
00:21:34,334 --> 00:21:35,586
REED: 15.

402
00:21:35,628 --> 00:21:38,005
ARCHER: THEY'RE BEING
DRAINED OF SOMETHING.

403
00:21:38,047 --> 00:21:41,134
WHOEVER DID IT
WENT TO A LOT OF TROUBLE.

404
00:21:41,175 --> 00:21:43,385
MY GUESS IS
THEY'RE COMING BACK.

405
00:21:43,427 --> 00:21:46,013
T'POL: WE SHOULD LEAVE.

406
00:21:46,055 --> 00:21:49,642
ARCHER: THERE ARE 15
DEAD PEOPLE OVER THERE.

407
00:21:49,683 --> 00:21:52,103
WE CAN'T LEAVE.

408
00:21:52,145 --> 00:21:54,188
T'POL: YOUR REASON
FOR BOARDING THAT VESSEL

409
00:21:54,230 --> 00:21:57,691
WAS TO PROVIDE ASSISTANCE
<i>IF</i> ASSISTANCE WAS REQUIRED.

410
00:21:57,733 --> 00:21:59,443
CLEARLY, IT NO LONGER IS.

411
00:21:59,485 --> 00:22:03,572
YOU'RE TELLING ME THAT WE
SHOULD JUST LEAVE THEM THERE?

412
00:22:03,614 --> 00:22:05,783
T'POL: WHAT'S THE ALTERNATIVE?

413
00:22:12,372 --> 00:22:15,126
YOUR INTENTIONS WERE
ADMIRABLE, CAPTAIN,

414
00:22:15,168 --> 00:22:18,004
BUT NOTHING CAN BE DONE
FOR THAT CREW NOW.

415
00:22:18,045 --> 00:22:21,924
AND IF WE REMAIN HERE,<i> YOUR</i> CREW
COULD BE PUT IN JEOPARDY.

416
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:33,477
[ BEEP ]

417
00:22:33,519 --> 00:22:34,645
ARCHER: ARCHER TO THE BRIDGE.

418
00:22:34,687 --> 00:22:38,232
TRAVIS: MAYWEATHER HERE, SIR.

419
00:22:38,274 --> 00:22:40,734
ARCHER: GO TO WARP 3.

420
00:22:40,776 --> 00:22:42,486
RESUME COURSE.

421
00:22:42,528 --> 00:22:43,529
TRAVIS: AYE, SIR.

422
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:57,501
PHLOX: NOT LONG AFTER
I BECAME A PHYSICIAN,

423
00:22:57,543 --> 00:22:58,919
THERE WAS AN EXPLOSION

424
00:22:58,961 --> 00:23:01,505
ON A CARGO SHIP
ORBITING MY HOMEWORLD.

425
00:23:01,547 --> 00:23:04,091
I WAS PART OF THE FIRST
MEDICAL TEAM TO ARRIVE.

426
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:08,346
THERE WERE 17 BODIES
ON THE BRIDGE ALONE.

427
00:23:08,386 --> 00:23:12,808
I'D NEVER SEEN THAT MANY DEAD
PEOPLE IN ONE PLACE BEFORE.

428
00:23:12,850 --> 00:23:14,768
VERY DISTURBING.

429
00:23:14,810 --> 00:23:16,520
YOU HAVE NOTHING
TO BE ASHAMED OF.

430
00:23:16,562 --> 00:23:18,772
I SCREAMED
LIKE A 12-YEAR-OLD.

431
00:23:18,814 --> 00:23:20,107
[ PHLOX CHUCKLES ]

432
00:23:20,149 --> 00:23:21,525
WE'RE ALL FRIGHTENED
BY UNFAMILIAR THINGS.

433
00:23:21,567 --> 00:23:25,738
YOU SHOULD BE GRATEFUL
THAT YOUR BODY OF EXPERIENCE

434
00:23:25,779 --> 00:23:28,949
DOESN'T INCLUDE
ROOMS FULL OF CORPSES.

435
00:23:28,991 --> 00:23:32,745
HOSHI: NOBODY ELSE SCREAMED.

436
00:23:32,786 --> 00:23:34,038
HAS SHE BEEN EATING?

437
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:35,289
PHLOX: NOT SO FAR.

438
00:23:35,331 --> 00:23:38,167
SHE HAS BEEN UNDER
A GREAT DEAL OF STRESS,

439
00:23:38,209 --> 00:23:41,628
BUT I'M HOPING THIS PROTEIN
CONCENTRATE WHETS HER APPETITE.

440
00:23:41,670 --> 00:23:42,629
HOSHI: I'M A TRANSLATOR.

441
00:23:42,671 --> 00:23:44,090
I DIDN'T COME OUT HERE

442
00:23:44,131 --> 00:23:46,050
TO SEE CORPSES
HANGING ON HOOKS.

443
00:23:46,092 --> 00:23:47,467
IT GOES WITHOUT SAYING

444
00:23:47,509 --> 00:23:49,553
THAT YOU'RE GOING TO ENCOUNTER
THE UNEXPECTED.

445
00:23:49,595 --> 00:23:51,764
NOT CORPSES ON HOOKS.

446
00:23:51,805 --> 00:23:52,973
HAVE YOU EVER CONSIDERED
THAT YOU MIGHT BE HAPPIER

447
00:23:53,015 --> 00:23:55,184
BACK AT THE UNIVERSITY,
TEACHING?

448
00:23:55,226 --> 00:23:58,436
I DID IT FOR YEARS.
IT WAS QUITE REWARDING.

449
00:24:01,607 --> 00:24:05,611
HOSHI: I'M AN EXOLINGUIST.
I GRADUATED SECOND IN MY CLASS.

450
00:24:05,652 --> 00:24:08,114
I SPENT THREE YEARS
IN STARFLEET TRAINING.

451
00:24:08,155 --> 00:24:11,617
I WAS JONATHAN ARCHER'S
FIRST CHOICE FOR THIS MISSION.

452
00:24:11,658 --> 00:24:13,911
EVERY INHABITED WORLD WE COME TO

453
00:24:13,953 --> 00:24:16,580
IS GOING TO BE FILLED
WITH LANGUAGE.

454
00:24:16,622 --> 00:24:20,458
SOME WILL HAVE HUNDREDS OF THEM.
HE NEEDS ME HERE.

455
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:22,753
IF SHE DOESN'T TAKE
THESE NUTRIENTS,

456
00:24:22,795 --> 00:24:24,422
I'M AFRAID SHE WON'T SURVIVE.

457
00:24:24,462 --> 00:24:25,714
HOSHI: ARE YOU SURE
THAT'S WHAT SHE EATS?

458
00:24:25,756 --> 00:24:27,341
PHLOX: IT'S CLOSE ENOUGH.

459
00:24:30,303 --> 00:24:32,596
HOSHI: I SHOULDN'T HAVE
BROUGHT HER ONBOARD.

460
00:24:32,638 --> 00:24:36,267
MAYBE I COULD ASK THE CAPTAIN
TO TRY TO FIND A PLANET

461
00:24:36,309 --> 00:24:38,227
WITH AN ARGON-RICH ATMOSPHERE.

462
00:24:38,269 --> 00:24:40,562
PHLOX: MIGHT BE EASIER
JUST TO FEED HER TO MY BAT.

463
00:24:40,604 --> 00:24:43,816
[ HOSHI SIGHS ]

464
00:24:43,857 --> 00:24:46,068
SHE NEEDS TO GET BACK
TO AN ENVIRONMENT

465
00:24:46,110 --> 00:24:47,485
THAT IS MORE SUITED TO HER.

466
00:24:47,527 --> 00:24:51,782
PHLOX: HMM. PERHAPS SOMEPLACE
WHERE SHE COULD TEACH.

467
00:24:58,705 --> 00:25:02,876
TUCKER: WHAT KIND
OF PASTA IS THIS?
IT'S GREAT.

468
00:25:02,918 --> 00:25:05,712
ARCHER: CHEF TOLD ME.
I DON'T REMEMBER.

469
00:25:05,754 --> 00:25:07,798
TUCKER: TOO SPICY FOR YOU?

470
00:25:07,840 --> 00:25:10,301
T'POL: IT'S FINE.

471
00:25:10,343 --> 00:25:12,761
TUCKER: MALCOLM'S ANXIOUS
TO RUN ANOTHER WEAPONS TEST,

472
00:25:12,803 --> 00:25:15,139
ESPECIALLY AFTER WHAT HAPPENED.

473
00:25:19,268 --> 00:25:20,227
TEA?

474
00:25:20,269 --> 00:25:22,438
T'POL: NO, THANK YOU.

475
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:23,897
TUCKER: CAPTAIN?

476
00:25:23,939 --> 00:25:26,608
ARCHER: SURE, THANKS.

477
00:25:26,650 --> 00:25:30,279
TUCKER: I HEARD
THEY WERE HUMANOID.

478
00:25:30,321 --> 00:25:31,780
IS THAT RIGHT?

479
00:25:31,822 --> 00:25:34,200
ARCHER: HUMANOID.

480
00:25:34,241 --> 00:25:36,827
TUCKER: DID THEY LOOK
ANYTHING LIKE US?

481
00:25:36,869 --> 00:25:38,204
ARCHER: THEY WERE IN UNIFORM.

482
00:25:39,955 --> 00:25:42,458
TUCKER: BUT YOU DIDN'T
RECOGNIZE THE SPECIES?

483
00:25:42,500 --> 00:25:45,669
THEY WERE CREWMEN,
MURDERED ON THEIR OWN SHIP.

484
00:25:45,711 --> 00:25:47,713
15 DEAD CREWMEN.

485
00:25:55,346 --> 00:25:58,057
I DETECTED A STELLAR NURSERY
ALONG OUR PRESENT COURSE.

486
00:25:58,098 --> 00:26:03,312
TUCKER: I SAW ONE ONCE THROUGH
THE BIG LENS OUTSIDE ANCHORAGE.

487
00:26:03,354 --> 00:26:06,815
A CLOSER VIEW MIGHT ALLEVIATE
SOME OF THE CREW'S TENSION.

488
00:26:06,857 --> 00:26:08,734
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

489
00:26:08,775 --> 00:26:10,568
THE TENSION BOTHERING YOU?

490
00:26:10,610 --> 00:26:12,570
NOT IN THE LEAST.

491
00:26:12,612 --> 00:26:18,952
MUST BE GREAT
NOT TO LET THINGS BOTHER YOU.

492
00:26:18,994 --> 00:26:22,456
NO REMORSE, NO GUILT.

493
00:26:23,999 --> 00:26:25,459
WHAT IF THEY WERE VULCANS?

494
00:26:25,501 --> 00:26:27,920
THINK YOU WOULD'VE REACTED
THE SAME WAY?

495
00:26:27,961 --> 00:26:29,796
THEY WEREN'T VULCANS.

496
00:26:29,838 --> 00:26:32,383
I SAID
<i>WHAT IF</i> THEY WERE VULCANS?

497
00:26:32,425 --> 00:26:34,718
WOULD YOU HAVE JUST
LEFT THEM THERE

498
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:36,803
HANGING LIKE
SLAUGHTERED ANIMALS?

499
00:26:36,845 --> 00:26:41,058
DON'T YOU THINK<i> MAYBE</i> 
YOU WOULD'VE TAKEN THEM DOWN,

500
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:43,601
TRIED TO FIGURE OUT
WHO THEY WERE,

501
00:26:43,643 --> 00:26:46,730
MADE SOME EFFORT
TO CONTACT THEIR FAMILIES?

502
00:26:46,772 --> 00:26:48,399
WE DON'T KNOW
WHERE THEY CAME FROM.

503
00:26:48,441 --> 00:26:51,777
IT WOULD BE VERY DIFFICULT
TO LOCATE THEIR FAMILIES.

504
00:26:51,818 --> 00:26:54,113
WE DIDN'T EVEN TRY.

505
00:26:58,700 --> 00:27:01,328
WHAT ABOUT YOU?
WHAT IF THEY WERE HUMANS?

506
00:27:01,370 --> 00:27:04,039
WOULD YOU JUST STICK YOUR TAIL
BETWEEN YOUR LEGS AND RUN?

507
00:27:04,081 --> 00:27:06,708
LEAVE THEM THERE TO ROT?

508
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:09,753
AM I THE ONLY ONE WHO'S HAVING
A PROBLEM WITH THIS?

509
00:27:09,795 --> 00:27:11,213
YOU SAID IT YOURSELF, SIR.

510
00:27:11,255 --> 00:27:14,467
WHOEVER KILLED THOSE PEOPLE
ARE PROBABLY COMING BACK.

511
00:27:14,508 --> 00:27:17,635
SO WE SHOULD AVOID
CONFRONTATION AT ANY COST.

512
00:27:17,677 --> 00:27:18,636
IS THAT WHAT YOU'RE SAYING?

513
00:27:18,678 --> 00:27:20,055
IS THAT WHAT YOU VULCANS DO?

514
00:27:20,097 --> 00:27:24,310
BURY YOUR HEADS IN THE SAND
AND THEN JUST FLY ON BY?

515
00:27:24,351 --> 00:27:27,771
WE VULCANS WOULD HAVE NEVER
GONE ONBOARD THAT SHIP

516
00:27:27,813 --> 00:27:28,772
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

517
00:27:28,814 --> 00:27:31,733
[ LAUGHS ] OH.

518
00:27:31,775 --> 00:27:33,651
YOU GOT AN ANSWER
FOR EVERYTHING, DON'T YOU?

519
00:27:33,693 --> 00:27:39,241
WE HAVE A CODE OF BEHAVIOR,
AND WE TRY TO OBEY IT.

520
00:27:42,369 --> 00:27:43,787
YOU MAY NOT BELIEVE THIS,

521
00:27:43,829 --> 00:27:48,834
BUT HUMANS HAVE
A CODE OF BEHAVIOR, TOO.

522
00:27:48,875 --> 00:27:50,127
IT TOOK A FEW THOUSAND YEARS,

523
00:27:50,169 --> 00:27:54,047
BUT I THINK WE'RE STARTING
TO GET IT RIGHT.

524
00:27:54,089 --> 00:27:56,842
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I ALMOST IGNORED IT.

525
00:27:59,845 --> 00:28:01,221
WE'VE REVERSED COURSE, SIR.

526
00:28:01,263 --> 00:28:04,183
WE SHOULD BE BACK AT
THE COORDINATES IN FIVE HOURS.

527
00:28:04,224 --> 00:28:06,226
ARCHER: YOU DON'T HAVE A PROBLEM
WITH THE ENVIRONMENTAL SUIT?

528
00:28:06,268 --> 00:28:08,646
PHLOX: NOT AT ALL.
ARCHER: GOOD.

529
00:28:08,686 --> 00:28:10,397
I'M GOING TO NEED YOU
TO EXAMINE THE BODIES,

530
00:28:10,439 --> 00:28:12,274
TRY TO IDENTIFY THEIR SPECIES.

531
00:28:12,316 --> 00:28:13,817
AND, WHILE YOU'RE AT IT,
IT WOULDN'T HURT

532
00:28:13,859 --> 00:28:15,319
IF YOU COULD FIGURE OUT
WHAT'S BEING DONE TO THEM.

533
00:28:15,361 --> 00:28:17,237
PHLOX: I'LL SEE WHAT
I CAN DO, CAPTAIN.

534
00:28:17,279 --> 00:28:18,656
ARCHER: YOU WANTED TO SEE
WHAT'S GOING ON OVER THERE.

535
00:28:18,696 --> 00:28:20,115
NOW'S YOUR CHANCE.

536
00:28:20,157 --> 00:28:22,034
I CAN'T THINK OF A BETTER WAY
TO FIND THEIR PEOPLE

537
00:28:22,075 --> 00:28:23,536
THAN THROUGH
THEIR OWN COM SYSTEM.

538
00:28:23,577 --> 00:28:25,538
YOU'RE GOING TO NEED TO GET IT
UP AND RUNNING.

539
00:28:25,579 --> 00:28:27,247
TUCKER: AYE, AYE, SIR.

540
00:28:27,289 --> 00:28:29,291
ARCHER: HOSHI'LL DECIPHER THEIR
LANGUAGE AND COMPOSE A MESSAGE.

541
00:28:29,333 --> 00:28:30,543
HOPEFULLY IT WILL MAKE SENSE.

542
00:28:30,584 --> 00:28:32,169
HOSHI: CAPTAIN.
ARCHER: I'M SORRY, ENSIGN.

543
00:28:32,211 --> 00:28:33,671
REED: I'LL BRING
A SECURITY DETAIL.

544
00:28:33,711 --> 00:28:35,214
ARCHER: THERE'S NO ONE
OVER THERE WHO CAN HURT US.

545
00:28:35,255 --> 00:28:37,883
STAY HERE AND WORK
ON THOSE TARGETING SCANNERS.

546
00:28:37,924 --> 00:28:43,847
PREPARE TO SUIT UP
AT...1400 HOURS.

547
00:28:43,889 --> 00:28:45,558
DISMISSED.

548
00:28:50,563 --> 00:28:53,065
ARCHER: HOW WERE THEY KILLED?
PHLOX: DIFFERENT WAYS.

549
00:28:53,106 --> 00:28:55,651
THIS ONE WAS GIVEN
A LETHAL DOSE OF CHLORAXINE.

550
00:28:55,693 --> 00:28:57,944
THE FIRST THREE BACK THERE
WERE SHOT--

551
00:28:57,986 --> 00:29:00,155
PARTICLE WEAPONS, I BELIEVE.

552
00:29:00,197 --> 00:29:04,243
THIS FELLOW HASN'T SUFFERED
AS MUCH CELLULAR DECAY.

553
00:29:04,284 --> 00:29:07,746
HE'S OUR BEST CANDIDATE
FOR A POSTMORTEM.

554
00:29:07,787 --> 00:29:09,373
CARE TO ASSIST?

555
00:29:13,669 --> 00:29:15,379
[ BUZZING ]

556
00:29:18,215 --> 00:29:20,259
[ WHIRRING ]

557
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:23,136
-[SPEAKING NATIVE LANGUAGE]
-YEAH.

558
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:30,894
HOSHI: MAYBE IT'S A LOG.
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

559
00:29:30,936 --> 00:29:32,104
TUCKER: BEATS ME.

560
00:29:32,145 --> 00:29:33,855
COULD BE A LAUNDRY LIST

561
00:29:33,897 --> 00:29:36,900
OR INSTRUCTIONS ON HOW
TO CONQUER THE UNIVERSE.

562
00:29:36,942 --> 00:29:42,322
[<i> SPEAKING NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

563
00:29:42,364 --> 00:29:45,492
THE GRAMMAR SOUNDS BIMODAL.

564
00:29:45,534 --> 00:29:47,703
THEIR TRANSCEIVER'S INTACT.

565
00:29:52,750 --> 00:29:55,210
LET'S HOPE THE NEXT TIME
WE MAKE FIRST CONTACT,

566
00:29:55,252 --> 00:29:59,172
IT ISN'T WITH A ROOM
FULL OF CORPSES.

567
00:29:59,214 --> 00:30:00,674
LET'S HOPE.

568
00:30:04,803 --> 00:30:05,929
HOSHI: SHIP.

569
00:30:05,971 --> 00:30:08,432
[ BUZZING ]

570
00:30:08,474 --> 00:30:09,683
SHIP.

571
00:30:09,725 --> 00:30:10,892
[ BUZZING ]

572
00:30:10,934 --> 00:30:13,979
PHLOX: JUST WHAT I THOUGHT.
ARCHER: WHAT?

573
00:30:14,020 --> 00:30:15,147
PHLOX: A ZYMUTH GLAND.

574
00:30:15,188 --> 00:30:17,274
IT RELEASES TRIGLOBULIN
INTO THE BLOOD.

575
00:30:17,316 --> 00:30:19,151
THAT'S WHAT ALL THESE
TUBES AND PUMPS ARE ABOUT.

576
00:30:19,192 --> 00:30:22,571
WHOEVER DID THIS IS TRYING
TO COLLECT TRIGLOBULIN.

577
00:30:22,613 --> 00:30:24,323
ARCHER: WHAT FOR?

578
00:30:24,364 --> 00:30:27,242
PHLOX: OH, ANY NUMBER
OF REASONS.
TO CREATE MEDICINES, VACCINES.

579
00:30:27,284 --> 00:30:29,244
SOME SPECIES
HAVE EVEN BEEN KNOWN

580
00:30:29,286 --> 00:30:31,497
TO USE IT AS AN APHRODISIAC.

581
00:30:31,538 --> 00:30:34,124
ARCHER: APHRODISIAC?
PHLOX: IT'S QUITE
A COMMON PRACTICE.

582
00:30:34,166 --> 00:30:36,835
I'M SURPRISED YOU'RE
NOT FAMILIAR WITH IT.

583
00:30:36,876 --> 00:30:40,880
HUMANS USED TO COLLECT
THE BILE OF BLACK BEARS,

584
00:30:40,922 --> 00:30:43,634
GRIND DOWN RHINO HORNS,
THINGS LIKE THAT,

585
00:30:43,676 --> 00:30:46,386
BUT NOT PEOPLE.

586
00:30:46,428 --> 00:30:48,972
IT'S WORTH NOTING
THAT TRIGLOBULIN IS VERY SIMILAR

587
00:30:49,014 --> 00:30:52,934
TO HUMAN LYMPHATIC FLUID.

588
00:30:52,976 --> 00:30:55,354
HOSHI: HOW LONG BEFORE
THE TRANSCEIVER'S ONLINE?

589
00:30:55,395 --> 00:30:58,440
TUCKER: A MINUTE OR TWO.

590
00:30:58,482 --> 00:31:01,819
I CAN'T GET ENOUGH OF THIS--
AN ALIEN SPACESHIP,

591
00:31:01,860 --> 00:31:04,946
SENDING OFF A MESSAGE
TO WHO KNOWS WHERE.

592
00:31:04,988 --> 00:31:06,865
HOSHI: THE QUICKER
WE GET THIS DONE,

593
00:31:06,906 --> 00:31:09,284
THE QUICKER WE CAN
GET BACK TO THE SHIP.

594
00:31:09,326 --> 00:31:11,787
TUCKER: IT'S YOUR SECOND AWAY
MISSION IN TWO DAYS.

595
00:31:11,829 --> 00:31:12,996
HOSHI: YEAH, GREAT.

596
00:31:13,038 --> 00:31:14,623
TUCKER: I WISH I HAD
AN EAR FOR LANGUAGES.

597
00:31:14,665 --> 00:31:17,710
THE CAPTAIN'S GONNA NEED
A TRANSLATOR WITH HIM

598
00:31:17,751 --> 00:31:19,961
A LOT MORE OFTEN
THAN AN ENGINEER.

599
00:31:20,003 --> 00:31:21,213
HOSHI: DISTRESS.

600
00:31:21,254 --> 00:31:23,799
[ BUZZING ]

601
00:31:26,051 --> 00:31:29,513
TWO OTHER TEACHERS AND I
ONCE TOOK A HYDRO-SKIMMER

602
00:31:29,555 --> 00:31:32,558
OUT ONTO A SMALL TRIBUTARY
IN THE AMAZON,

603
00:31:32,599 --> 00:31:35,811
YOU KNOW, TO SEE THE WILDLIFE--
SLOTHS, PINK DOLPHINS,

604
00:31:35,853 --> 00:31:37,020
ALL KINDS OF SNAKES.

605
00:31:37,062 --> 00:31:39,939
TUCKER: WOW.
HOSHI: IT GAVE ME THE CREEPS.

606
00:31:39,981 --> 00:31:42,067
IF I DIDN'T LIKE
BEING AROUND ANACONDAS,

607
00:31:42,108 --> 00:31:44,194
YOU CAN IMAGINE
HOW I FEEL ABOUT SULIBAN

608
00:31:44,236 --> 00:31:47,072
OR WHOEVER BUTCHERED
THE CREW OF THIS SHIP.

609
00:31:49,408 --> 00:31:52,452
I'M GONNA ASK THE CAPTAIN
TO TAKE ME HOME.

610
00:31:54,788 --> 00:31:56,289
YOU SERIOUS?

611
00:31:56,331 --> 00:31:58,333
I SHOULD HAVE NEVER LEFT
THE UNIVERSITY.

612
00:31:58,375 --> 00:32:00,085
I'M NOT SUITED FOR THIS.

613
00:32:00,126 --> 00:32:03,171
TUCKER: GIVE IT A TRY.
YOU'LL BE FINE.

614
00:32:03,213 --> 00:32:05,507
HOSHI: YOU WEREN'T
HERE YESTERDAY.

615
00:32:05,549 --> 00:32:09,010
I SAW THOSE BODIES
AND FELL APART.

616
00:32:09,052 --> 00:32:12,055
THE CAPTAIN NEEDS
A TRANSLATOR HE CAN COUNT ON,

617
00:32:12,097 --> 00:32:15,016
SOMEONE WHO SHOWS A LITTLE GRACE
UNDER PRESSURE.

618
00:32:15,058 --> 00:32:16,309
THAT ISN'T ME.

619
00:32:16,351 --> 00:32:18,061
YOU CAN'T BE SURE OF THAT.

620
00:32:18,103 --> 00:32:22,148
OH, YES, I CAN.

621
00:32:22,190 --> 00:32:23,650
DISTRESS.

622
00:32:23,692 --> 00:32:24,651
[ BEEPING ]

623
00:32:24,693 --> 00:32:29,907
[<i> SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE</i> ]

624
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:30,990
DISTRESS.

625
00:32:31,032 --> 00:32:32,576
[<i> SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE</i> ]

626
00:32:32,618 --> 00:32:35,120
I THINK I'VE GOT IT.

627
00:32:35,161 --> 00:32:37,706
SHIP IN DISTRESS.

628
00:32:37,748 --> 00:32:41,794
[<i> SPEAKS NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

629
00:32:41,835 --> 00:32:43,002
[ BEEPING ]

630
00:32:43,044 --> 00:32:46,465
[<i> SPEAKS NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

631
00:32:52,053 --> 00:32:53,764
T'POL: T'POL TO ARCHER.

632
00:32:53,806 --> 00:32:55,140
GO AHEAD.

633
00:32:55,181 --> 00:32:57,100
T'POL: THERE'S A VESSEL
APPROACHING, CAPTAIN.

634
00:32:57,142 --> 00:32:58,351
ITS POWER SIGNATURES

635
00:32:58,393 --> 00:33:00,479
MATCH THE SCANS YOU TOOK
OF THOSE BIO-PUMPS.

636
00:33:00,520 --> 00:33:04,149
IT APPEARS THAT WHOEVER
KILLED THAT CREW HAS RETURNED.

637
00:33:04,190 --> 00:33:05,984
ARCHER: TIME TO GO, DOC.

638
00:33:11,531 --> 00:33:14,910
ARCHER: TRIP, HOSHI,
DOCKING HATCH NOW.

639
00:33:22,584 --> 00:33:25,128
DISTANCE--60,000 KILOMETERS.

640
00:33:25,170 --> 00:33:27,840
T'POL: BRIDGE TO ARMORY.
REED: ARMORY.

641
00:33:27,881 --> 00:33:31,092
WE HAVE A POTENTIALLY
HOSTILE VESSEL APPROACHING.

642
00:33:31,134 --> 00:33:33,094
ARE YOU PREPARED
TO DEFEND THE SHIP?

643
00:33:33,136 --> 00:33:35,430
THAT DEPENDS.
HOW LONG TILL IT GETS HERE?

644
00:33:35,472 --> 00:33:37,599
TRAVIS: 10 MINUTES, MAYBE LESS.

645
00:33:37,641 --> 00:33:39,893
THEN THE ANSWER
IS MOST LIKELY NO.

646
00:33:39,935 --> 00:33:42,437
THE SCANNERS
ARE STILL OUT OF ALIGNMENT.

647
00:33:42,479 --> 00:33:44,982
LOOK, IF YOU WANTED ME TO HIT
A STATIONARY DAIRY BARN,

648
00:33:45,064 --> 00:33:47,150
THEN I COULD ACCOMMODATE YOU,
BUT NOT A MOVING VESSEL.

649
00:33:47,192 --> 00:33:48,401
DO THE BEST YOU CAN,

650
00:33:48,443 --> 00:33:51,613
BUT I NEED YOU ON THE BRIDGE
IN FIVE MINUTES.

651
00:33:55,367 --> 00:33:58,787
ARCHER: ARCHER TO T'POL.
DEPLOY THE DOCKING ARM.

652
00:33:58,829 --> 00:34:01,039
ARM EXTENDED.

653
00:34:01,080 --> 00:34:02,875
ARCHER: HOW CLOSE ARE THEY?

654
00:34:02,916 --> 00:34:04,167
8,000 KILOMETERS.

655
00:34:04,209 --> 00:34:05,544
ARCHER: WHAT KIND OF WEAPONS?

656
00:34:05,585 --> 00:34:09,088
OUR SENSORS
CAN'T PENETRATE THEIR SHIELDING.

657
00:34:09,130 --> 00:34:10,423
HAVE YOU TRIED HAILING THEM?

658
00:34:10,465 --> 00:34:11,383
T'POL: YES.

659
00:34:11,424 --> 00:34:13,176
THERE'S BEEN NO RESPONSE.

660
00:34:13,218 --> 00:34:14,678
TRY AGAIN.

661
00:34:20,684 --> 00:34:22,101
THE POD'S ON THE ARM.

662
00:34:23,979 --> 00:34:25,146
T'POL TO ARCHER.

663
00:34:25,188 --> 00:34:27,399
THEY'RE STILL NOT RESPONDING.

664
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:29,067
REED: THEY'RE CHARGING WEAPONS.

665
00:34:31,361 --> 00:34:33,530
THEY'RE TARGETING OUR ENGINES.

666
00:34:33,572 --> 00:34:36,157
ARCHER: WE'RE ALMOST IN.
STAND BY TO JUMP TO WARP.

667
00:35:02,267 --> 00:35:03,476
ARCHER: DOORS.

668
00:35:16,698 --> 00:35:17,950
ARCHER: ARCHER TO THE BRIDGE.

669
00:35:17,991 --> 00:35:20,452
IT DOESN'T FEEL LIKE
WE'VE GONE TO WARP.

670
00:35:20,493 --> 00:35:24,623
T'POL: OUR PORT NACELLE
HAS BEEN DAMAGED.

671
00:35:24,664 --> 00:35:27,626
ARCHER: HAVE MALCOLM
ARM THE TORPEDOES.

672
00:35:32,965 --> 00:35:34,173
REPORT.

673
00:35:34,215 --> 00:35:35,634
TRAVIS: WE'RE DEAD
IN THE WATER, SIR.

674
00:35:35,675 --> 00:35:37,510
T'POL: THEY SEEM TO HAVE
STOPPED FIRING.

675
00:35:37,552 --> 00:35:38,678
THEY'RE CLOSING
ON OUR POSITION.

676
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:40,013
ARCHER: MALCOLM?

677
00:35:40,055 --> 00:35:42,140
REED: BOTH FORWARD TUBES
LOADED AND READY, SIR.

678
00:35:44,059 --> 00:35:46,728
ARCHER: STAND BY STARBOARD TUBE.
REED: YES, SIR.

679
00:35:47,980 --> 00:35:49,106
FIRE.

680
00:36:00,241 --> 00:36:02,327
ARCHER: STAND BY PORT TUBE.

681
00:36:02,368 --> 00:36:03,286
REED: READY.

682
00:36:03,328 --> 00:36:04,663
FIRE.

683
00:36:13,296 --> 00:36:15,381
ARCHER: TRIP,
WARP STATUS.

684
00:36:15,423 --> 00:36:17,467
TUCKER: THE NACELLE'S BEEN
COMPLETELY DEPOLARIZED.

685
00:36:17,509 --> 00:36:19,427
I'M AFRAID WE'RE
STUCK HERE FOR A WHILE.

686
00:36:19,469 --> 00:36:20,428
[ BUZZING ]

687
00:36:20,470 --> 00:36:21,972
[ HOSHI GASPS ]

688
00:36:25,558 --> 00:36:26,810
TRAVIS: WHAT WAS THAT?

689
00:36:26,852 --> 00:36:29,395
PHLOX: A SUBMOLECULAR BIO-SCAN.

690
00:36:29,437 --> 00:36:32,482
YOU'VE BEEN PROBED, ENSIGN.

691
00:36:32,524 --> 00:36:34,317
WE'VE ALL BEEN PROBED.

692
00:36:34,359 --> 00:36:35,944
THEY HAVE NO DOUBT DISCOVERED

693
00:36:35,986 --> 00:36:40,157
THAT YOUR LYMPHATIC SYSTEMS
CONTAIN SOME USEFUL COMPOUNDS.

694
00:36:48,373 --> 00:36:49,624
ARCHER: GET TO THE ARMORY.

695
00:36:49,666 --> 00:36:51,918
START DISTRIBUTING
HAND WEAPONS.

696
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:56,339
POST SECURITY TEAMS AT LEVEL--
[ BEEPING ]

697
00:36:56,381 --> 00:36:58,216
TRAVIS: SIR, ANOTHER VESSEL
JUST DROPPED OUT OF WARP.

698
00:36:58,257 --> 00:37:01,302
TRAVIS: THEY'RE ON
AN INTERCEPT COURSE.
ARCHER: LET'S SEE IT.

699
00:37:04,389 --> 00:37:05,891
[ BEEPING ]

700
00:37:05,932 --> 00:37:07,893
HOSHI: THEY'RE HAILING US.

701
00:37:07,934 --> 00:37:09,936
ARCHER: PUT IT UP.

702
00:37:09,978 --> 00:37:12,271
[<i> SPEAKS NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

703
00:37:12,313 --> 00:37:14,357
[ ARCHER SIGHS ]
T'POL: CAPTAIN?

704
00:37:14,399 --> 00:37:16,735
ARCHER: HE'S FROM THE SAME
SPECIES AS THE MURDERED CREW.

705
00:37:16,776 --> 00:37:18,528
THEY MUST'VE PICKED UP
YOUR DISTRESS CALL.

706
00:37:18,570 --> 00:37:20,446
[<i> SPEAKS NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

707
00:37:20,488 --> 00:37:22,115
ARCHER: TELL HIM
THE SHIP ABOVE US

708
00:37:22,157 --> 00:37:24,617
KILLED THE CREW
OF THE CARGO VESSEL.

709
00:37:24,659 --> 00:37:27,120
THEY'RE ABOUT
TO DO THE SAME TO US.

710
00:37:27,162 --> 00:37:30,331
[ BEEPING ]

711
00:37:30,373 --> 00:37:33,585
I TOLD HIM WHAT YOU SAID, SIR,
BUT I DOUBT IT MADE ANY SENSE.

712
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:35,128
ARCHER: WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

713
00:37:35,170 --> 00:37:37,797
THIS ISN'T EXACTLY SPANISH
WE'RE DEALING WITH HERE.

714
00:37:37,839 --> 00:37:41,051
I'D BE LUCKY IF I'M GETTING
HALF THE VOCABULARY RIGHT.

715
00:37:46,139 --> 00:37:48,934
REED: THEY'VE LOCKED ON TO US
WITH SOME KIND OF
STABILIZING BEAM.

716
00:37:48,975 --> 00:37:51,644
ARCHER: USE THE IMPULSE ENGINES.
GET US THE HELL OUT OF HERE.

717
00:37:51,686 --> 00:37:53,146
TRAVIS: I CAN'T, SIR.

718
00:37:53,188 --> 00:37:55,314
THEIR BEAM'S DISRUPTING
ALL OUR PROPULSION SYSTEMS.

719
00:37:55,356 --> 00:37:59,152
[<i> SPEAKS NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

720
00:37:59,194 --> 00:38:02,405
HOSHI: IT SEEMS HE GOT
THE PART ABOUT
KILLING THE CARGO-SHIP CREW,

721
00:38:02,447 --> 00:38:03,823
BUT HE BELIEVES WE DID IT, SIR.

722
00:38:03,865 --> 00:38:05,408
A-AT LEAST I THINK HE DOES.

723
00:38:05,450 --> 00:38:08,161
T'POL: TELL HIM WE SENT
THE DISTRESS CALL.

724
00:38:08,203 --> 00:38:11,289
WHY WOULD WE KILL HIS PEOPLE
AND THEN DO THAT?

725
00:38:13,833 --> 00:38:16,920
[<i> SPEAKS NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

726
00:38:16,962 --> 00:38:18,421
I THINK I UNDERSTOOD THIS ONE.

727
00:38:18,463 --> 00:38:21,424
HE SAYS THE DISTRESS CALL
CAME FROM HIS SHIP, NOT OURS.

728
00:38:21,466 --> 00:38:23,301
WE NEEDED THEIR FREQUENCIES.

729
00:38:23,342 --> 00:38:26,805
GOING THERE WAS
THE ONLY WAY TO FIND THEM.

730
00:38:28,681 --> 00:38:30,934
[<i> SPEAKS NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

731
00:38:30,976 --> 00:38:32,393
SOMETHING ABOUT DNA SCANS.

732
00:38:32,435 --> 00:38:35,063
HE WANTS TO KNOW WHY WE
WERE THERE TWO YEARS AGO.

733
00:38:35,105 --> 00:38:36,064
TWO YEARS AGO?

734
00:38:36,106 --> 00:38:38,233
HE PROBABLY MEANS TWO DAYS, SIR.

735
00:38:38,275 --> 00:38:41,360
THE PHONETIC PROCESSOR IS
STILL HAVING TROUBLE LOCKING ON.

736
00:38:41,402 --> 00:38:43,529
[<i> SPEAKS NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

737
00:38:43,571 --> 00:38:47,742
I'M NOT CERTAIN, BUT I DON'T
THINK HE'S GONNA HELP US.

738
00:38:47,784 --> 00:38:50,453
REED: THEY'RE 50 METERS
ABOVE US.

739
00:38:50,495 --> 00:38:51,830
49.

740
00:38:53,498 --> 00:38:55,458
ARCHER: THE PUMPS.

741
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:58,044
TELL THEM TO RUN SCANS

742
00:38:58,086 --> 00:39:00,880
ON THE BIO-PUMPS THAT ARE
HOOKED UP TO THE CORPSES.

743
00:39:00,922 --> 00:39:03,133
THEY'LL SEE
THEY'RE NOT OUR TECHNOLOGY.

744
00:39:03,175 --> 00:39:05,343
HAVE THEM COMPARE
THE POWER SIGNATURES

745
00:39:05,384 --> 00:39:08,013
TO THE SHIP THAT'S ABOUT
TO LAND ON OUR ROOF.

746
00:39:08,054 --> 00:39:09,764
WHERE ARE THEY, MALCOLM?

747
00:39:09,806 --> 00:39:12,225
THEY'VE STOPPED
AT ABOUT 10 METERS.

748
00:39:15,394 --> 00:39:17,730
HOSHI: I'M HAVING TROUBLE
WITH THE WORD "PUMPS," SIR.

749
00:39:17,772 --> 00:39:20,150
I'VE GOT THE PROCESSOR
SEARCHING FOR SYNONYMS.

750
00:39:20,192 --> 00:39:22,360
[<i> SPEAKS NATIVE LANGUAGE</i> ]

751
00:39:22,401 --> 00:39:24,696
THE TRANSLATOR'S NOT MAKING A
WHOLE LOT OF SENSE TO HIM, SIR.

752
00:39:24,737 --> 00:39:26,114
HE'S GETTING FRUSTRATED.

753
00:39:26,156 --> 00:39:27,615
I THINK HE'S RUNNING
OUT OF PATIENCE, CAPTAIN.

754
00:39:27,657 --> 00:39:30,994
ARCHER: THEN FORGET
THE TRANSLATOR.
DO IT YOURSELF.

755
00:39:31,036 --> 00:39:33,454
HOSHI: DO WHAT MYSELF?
ARCHER: TALK TO HIM.

756
00:39:33,496 --> 00:39:35,081
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE, SIR.

757
00:39:35,123 --> 00:39:39,127
I-I-I HAVEN'T EVEN LEARNED
THEIR BASIC CONJUGATIONS.

758
00:39:39,169 --> 00:39:41,462
TALK TO HIM, HOSHI.
IT DOESN'T HAVE TO BE PERFECT.

759
00:39:41,504 --> 00:39:44,507
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND. I DON'T
EVEN KNOW HOW TO SAY "PUMP."

760
00:39:44,549 --> 00:39:46,343
I'LL GET IT ALL WRONG.

761
00:39:46,384 --> 00:39:49,470
IT'LL--IT'LL JUST
MAKE THINGS WORSE.

762
00:39:49,512 --> 00:39:51,472
THINGS CAN'T GET MUCH WORSE.

763
00:39:51,514 --> 00:39:52,932
SIR.

764
00:39:56,519 --> 00:39:57,979
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

765
00:39:58,021 --> 00:40:01,024
REED: CAPTAIN, THEY'VE STARTED
DRILLING INTO THE HULL.

766
00:40:02,567 --> 00:40:03,985
HOSHI, HOSHI.

767
00:40:04,027 --> 00:40:06,654
I NEED YOU TO DO THIS.

768
00:40:06,696 --> 00:40:08,698
WE ALL DO.

769
00:40:08,740 --> 00:40:10,992
THAT'S WHY YOU'RE HERE.

770
00:40:26,341 --> 00:40:29,344
[ CONVERSATION
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE ]

771
00:40:39,604 --> 00:40:41,106
ARCHER: AGAIN.

772
00:41:00,959 --> 00:41:02,001
ARCHER: WHAT'D HE SAY?

773
00:41:06,965 --> 00:41:08,133
ARCHER: ENSIGN.

774
00:41:14,889 --> 00:41:16,849
[ BEEPING ]

775
00:41:16,891 --> 00:41:18,977
REED: THEY'RE TARGETING
THE VESSEL ABOVE US.

776
00:41:24,649 --> 00:41:26,109
TRAVIS: WE'VE GOT IMPULSE BACK.

777
00:41:26,151 --> 00:41:27,110
ARCHER: MOVE US AWAY.

778
00:41:27,152 --> 00:41:28,403
REED: CAPTAIN, I MAY BE WRONG,

779
00:41:28,445 --> 00:41:30,738
BUT I THINK I'VE GOT
THE SCANNERS ALIGNED.

780
00:41:30,780 --> 00:41:32,615
PERMISSION TO LAUNCH
A TORPEDO.

781
00:41:32,657 --> 00:41:34,367
GRANTED.

782
00:41:47,380 --> 00:41:50,758
ARCHER: NICE OF THEM TO WAIT
TILL WE GOT CLEAR.

783
00:41:50,800 --> 00:41:52,677
ALL STOP.

784
00:41:59,851 --> 00:42:02,854
I THINK WE MAY HAVE
JUST MADE A FRIEND...

785
00:42:05,064 --> 00:42:06,983
THANKS TO YOU.

786
00:42:13,614 --> 00:42:17,118
ARCHER:
CAPTAIN'S STARLOG, MAY 6, 2151.

787
00:42:17,160 --> 00:42:19,537
AFTER HELPING THEM RECOVER
THEIR DEAD CREWMEN,

788
00:42:19,578 --> 00:42:22,707
WE HAD A CHANCE TO SPEND
SOME TIME WITH THE AXANAR.

789
00:42:22,748 --> 00:42:26,752
TURNS OUT THEY'RE ANDROGYNOUS
AND LIVE OVER 400 YEARS.

790
00:42:26,794 --> 00:42:28,880
I LOOK FORWARD
TO MEETING THEM AGAIN

791
00:42:28,921 --> 00:42:30,673
UNDER BETTER CIRCUMSTANCES.

792
00:42:30,715 --> 00:42:32,008
BEFORE WE RESUME OUR COURSE,

793
00:42:32,050 --> 00:42:35,178
I'VE AGREED
TO MAKE A BRIEF DETOUR.

794
00:42:50,693 --> 00:42:54,655
THIS ISN'T EXACTLY
LIKE THE PLACE YOU CAME FROM,

795
00:42:54,697 --> 00:42:57,200
BUT IT'S CLOSE ENOUGH.

796
00:42:57,242 --> 00:42:59,911
IT'S NOT THAT HARD TO ADAPT.

797
00:43:02,997 --> 00:43:04,957
YOU'RE GONNA DO JUST FINE HERE.
